node.text:
Reflect with us 💭

🗣 Join the conversation between Sage and Jazz (@just_found_out_im_hot ) about the intersection of queer identity and disability with kink/rope. This is an important discussion that we hope you can learn something from. 

🤟🏼 Huge thank you to @the.blaike for ASL interpretation for this LIVE! 

🖊 The comment section is open for questions, thoughts or feedback.

🔏 Please be kind and mindful of the language that you use! We welcome conflict or disagreement as an opportunity for deeper relationship building and also ask that you try to hold other perspectives to be true and valid at the same time as yours. 

@authenticallysage 
@callme.sage 🌿💕

Join us for a discussion about our ongoing Monday DEI spaces with @authenticallysage @callme.sage 💕

We look forward to building with you, learning along side you and creating change together. 🙏🏼

The practice of Hashira Shibari draws its inspiration from the very architecture of Japan’s traditional houses, where an abundance of beams and pillars provided an instant framework for tying. 

In our long-awaited Hashira series, @tamanduakinbaku will teach three variations of floor-based Hashira positions, two anchor point options, and present a mesmerising free-tying session and share his insights on the inspiration and intention to be found in the rigidity and restrictiveness of Hashira.

Floorplay tutorials and Anchor Points dropping Wednesday. Free-tying session coming up on Friday! And just because we’re not the type to leave you hanging (well, not too long anyway), here’s a teaser of what you can expect in the incredible free-tying video with model @mie.neko.rope✨

In this NEW class, @ropunawa teaches the Choker Tie. 

🧶 By attaching the hands and arms to the neck, chest, and body, this advanced class explores one of the most erogenous areas for intense play. 

💕While the choker tie doesn’t incorporate breath play, it is a powerful experience and tricky to do right. We insist that students do not reproduce this tie unless they have extensive experience.

DEI* Monday Discussion: 

🎉 TOPICS OF INTEREST 🎉

We would love to invite you all to share in the comments topic(s) of interest and people who may be interested in collaborating on posts! My voice is not the only voice in this space nor the most important. I certainly don’t have all the knowledge on all topics related to DEI. Id love to connect with others interested in sharing! P.S. don’t let that imposter syndrome get you - drop your own name below if you have things you want to share! 💕🌿

CONTEXT: I want to take a moment to talk about context and intention as it’s been brought up in the comments. All of the DEI Monday posts are here to encourage reflective thinking - not about being right or wrong. I am not trying to be “right” or superior in these posts. The intention is to provide information, share resources and encourage collective dialogue and discourse. I am not perfect and I’m always open to feedback if the language or way I frame the context isn’t inviting that into the space. We are all a work in progress, myself and Shibari Study included.

We’d love to be in community conversation with you! Check the last slides to share your thoughts in the comments! 🌿

As always, we welcome dialogue in the comments to discuss but ask that everyone please be kind and mindful of the language they are using if they disagree. This is a place to be in conversation and build community together through discourse. We welcome conflict or disagreement as an opportunity for deeper relationship building and also ask that you try to hold other perspectives to be true and valid at the same time as yours.

xo,
Sage 💕
@authenticallysage 

*Diversity, Equity and Inclusion

DEI* Monday Discussion: 

🎉 COMMUNITY UPLIFTING 🎉

We would love to invite you all to share in the comments below about impactful people you’ve experienced in your journey and in our rope community! The slides will provide prompts if that’s helpful, or you can share whatever resonates for you! 💕🌿

CONTEXT: I want to take a moment to talk about context and intention as it’s been brought up in the comments. All of the DEI Monday posts are here to encourage reflective thinking - not about being right or wrong. I am not trying to be “right” or superior in these posts. The intention is to provide information, share resources and encourage collective dialogue and discourse. I am not perfect and I’m always open to feedback if the language or way I frame the context isn’t inviting that into the space. We are all a work in progress, myself and Shibari Study included.

We’d love to be in community conversation with you! Check the last slides to share your thoughts in the comments! 🌿

As always, we welcome dialogue in the comments to discuss but ask that everyone please be kind and mindful of the language they are using if they disagree. This is a place to be in conversation and build community together through discourse. We welcome conflict or disagreement as an opportunity for deeper relationship building and also ask that you try to hold other perspectives to be true and valid at the same time as yours.

xo,
Sage 💕
@authenticallysage 

*Diversity, Equity and Inclusion
